hopobject.body: Who would I report to? cialis daily costco Using the ESO's Very Large Telescope, scientists first discovered the gas cloud in 2011. At the time, this object was much cooler than the surrounding stars (only about 280 degrees Celsius), and was composed mostly of hydrogen and helium. It is a dusty, ionized gas cloud, and glows under the strong ultraviolet radiation from the hot stars around it in the crowded heart of the Milky Way. Now, this cloud of material is making its closest approach, becoming grossly stretched by the black hole's extreme gravitational field.
